    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Cnicus benedictus are its bioactive compounds, which include saponins like cnicoside A and cnicoside B that exhibit anti-inflammatory properties and are known to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines. Additionally, the plant contains phenolic acids such as chlorogenic acid and caffeic acid, which possess antioxidant and antimicrobial activities, and flavonoids with known anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory effects. Cnicus benedictus also contains alkaloids like cnicin, which have been reported to exhibit anti-inflammatory and antifungal activities. Furthermore, the plant is a rich source of coumarins, which have been shown to exhibit anticoagulant and anti-inflammatory effects. These bioactive compounds contribute to the medicinal properties of Cnicus benedictus, including its anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant activities.",
